NAME
	mem-gauge (display) - render per-pool used/max horizontal bars parsed from a /dev/memory-format snapshot file

INTERFACE
	display (MatrixDisplay)

READS
	mem/current	verbatim /dev/memory format, one line per pool:
			cursize maxsize hw nalloc nfree nbrk poolmax name
			(cursize, maxsize, name used; first 8 pools kept)

WRITES
	none (renders only)

DESCRIPTION
	One labelled horizontal bar per pool, values shown in KB.  A bar
	recolours when occupancy exceeds 80 percent.  Pools with maxsize
	<= 0 are skipped.  Re-reads on every update tick.  No pointer or
	key handling.

SEE ALSO
	sysmon-svc (produces mem/current in its outdir)
